This paper deals with domain adaptation in computer vision, specifically in the context of car recognition in surveillance images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel regularization technique, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also uses deep neural networks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also deals with image synthesis and manipulation, which falls under the category of multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another likely category. Finally, the paper deals with surveillance images, which falls under the category of cryptography and security, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) another possible category.
